The paper discusses the modelling of activation functions in artificial neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper explores the use of small neural networks to learn the activation functions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of activation functions is also relevant in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI).
